18/12/2002
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Some 500 new personnel will join the police by the year's end, along with another 500 next year, Minister of Local Self-Government Aleksandar Gestakovski said Tuesday (17 December).
They will include Macedonians and Albanians, as required by the Ohrid peace accord.
In other news Tuesday, leaders of the Democratic Union for Integration elected Gzim Ostreni as the new general secretary of the party.
He will succeed Deputy Prime Minister Musa Xhaferi.
(Utrinski Vesnik - 18/12/02;
A1 TV, MIA, Makfax, SEEurope.net - 17/12/02)
